{"id":936511716,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"4 months, 3 weeks","timestamp":1681928241,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"167 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/936511716/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Multiply Strings","memory":"13.8 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def multiply(self, num1: str, num2: str) -> str:\n        if num1 == '0' or num2 == '0':\n            return '0'\n        n, m = len(num1), len(num2)\n        output = deque([0] * (n + m - 1))\n\n        for i, j in product(range(n - 1, -1, -1), range(m - 1, -1, -1)):\n            mul = int(num1[i]) * int(num2[j]) + output[i + j]\n            output[i + j] = mul % 10\n            if i + j - 1 >= 0:\n                output[i + j - 1] += mul // 10\n            else:\n                output.appendleft(mul // 10)\n        while output[0] == 0:\n            output.popleft()\n        \n        return ''.join(map(str, output))\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"multiply-strings","has_notes":true,"flag_type":1}
